<br>
Most equipment sites don't list this as a searchable feature, unless I've missed one.<br>
<br>
Also, what besides a Glowing Stone Band, or the Magician summoned items give Ultravision or Infravision?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulyberniabelisama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lybernia Belisama</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://cwm.ragesofsanity.com/otn/happy/icon13.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/4/01 10:44:44 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/sherilyn70/lybernia4a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Light sources</span><hr size=1> Fire Beetle Eye<br>
Lightstone<br>
Greater Lightstone<br>
Stein of Moggok <br>
Klezendian Crystal (+10 mana, range slot)<br>
Shiny Brass Shield <br>
Slithini's Shield<br>
Charred Guardian Shield (+9 wis)<br>
Glowing Wooden Crook <br>
Screaming Mace<br>
Bloodforge Hammer<br>
Splitpaw Mask<br>
<br>
Those are just the ones I know of.. there could be more<br>
<br>
Items with Serpent Sight:<br>
Crown of King Tranix <br>
Glowing Stone Band <br>
Ring of the Frozen Flame<br>
<br>
Potions for Serpent Sight: <br>
Serpent's Conviction<br>
<br>
